org.apache.paimon.types

Class ArrayType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.paimon.types.DataType
      • org.apache.paimon.types.ArrayType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @Public
public final class ArrayType
extends DataType
    Data type of an array of elements with same subtype. Compared to the SQL standard, the maximum cardinality of an array cannot be specified but is fixed at Integer.MAX_VALUE. Also, any valid type is supported as a subtype.
    Since:
    0.4.0
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
